5:
Now then, may this party be an
enjoyable one. Cheers.
15:
This food is so delicious... I'd love a
drink with it... but I must resist!
Alcohol would pair so well with these
dishes, though!
19: It looks like you are all having fun.
29:
That's right. I am Suizen, the Chair of
the Diviners' Commission. It's nice to
finally get a chance to talk with you.
33:
I... Um... Y-yes, it's an honor to
f-finally meet you!
46:
Hey, you diviner doo-doo head! Stop
bothering my Suzuka this instant!
50:
Since when is she "yours"... I was
simply making conversation.
58:
Y-yes. We're definitely just talking...
Probably.
63:
Then I will allow it! But if you need
anything, give a holler, you hear me?
68:
*sigh* You're like the boss I've
always wanted but never had!
74:
And here I thought we could have a
quiet conversation. I should have
known better...
78:
Hm? Inaho, what's that bottle you're
holding?
83:
Oh, this ol' thing? This contains a
sacred nectar known as the Waters
of Ecstasy!
87:
Since you cannot drink alcohol, I
brought this as an alternative for
you!
99:
Ahahaha! Look at the plates! I can
really dish out a good performance,
can't I?
111:
Ah, geez... Not again... Inaho, what
did you give her?
115:
I-I just gave her a drink from my
mother's collection—
121:
Are you talking about the Waters of
Ecstasy? That liquid has an
intoxicating effect on humans!
129: Hehe, you two are just so adorable...
133:
Two... Two cutie-pies in a league all
their own!
142:
We've got our work cut out for us,
Mizuchi.
146: Wait a minute... Where's little Suizen?
150:
Ah... Maybe he had some work to
take care of?
155:
But I didn't even get to pinch his
cheeks! We should go find him!
160:
To get like that after a few drinks,
she must have had a lot bottled up
inside.
164:
Or perhaps she was always like that.
You all would know, correct?
167:
So you were aware of our presence...
Are you mocking us?
170:
You were pretty obvious. Did you
think this would be easy? We have a
fugitive ninja, a celestial maiden,
and the Diviners' Commission on our
side, you know.
176:
Y-you little... How DARE you look
down on us!
179:
Ah, I spy with my little eye... our
adorable Suizen!
183:
So this is where you were! We were
looking all over for you, you know!
187:
Um, looks we're interrupting your
work after all.
191:
Well, yes, but your entrance has
spoiled the dramatic atmosphere a
bit.
197:
Hm? What're you guys doing here?
You on vacation too?
201:
Forsaking your ninja way has
disgraced you! I cannot bear the
sight of such disgusting tomfoolery!
You must be disposed of!
204: Fall into the dark depths of—
206:
What the—
Suzukaze, you dare to—
211: Ugh, will you just SHUT UP already!
214:
You just keep yapping, and I'm sick
of it! All you're doing is reminding
me of all the bad times, just when I
was having fun!
218: Well, I've had it up to HERE with you!
224:
I've been wanting to say this for a
long, LONG time...
227:
You're too damn gloomy! The whole
lot of you! All this talk about
forsaking this, and betraying that,
and blah, blah, BLAH!
230:
But if ONE person complains to their
superior or anyone else, THEY'RE the
bad guy! What kinda sense does
that make?!
236:
What's so disgusting about me,
anyway?! I'll have you know these
clothes were picked out for me by
my friends! I've never been better!
245:
Were you planning on taking them
all out on your own?
249: I was just out for a stroll. I promise.
252:
You can play with your former
colleagues to your heart's content.
The commission will take care of the
rest.
262: By the way... Can I pinch your cheeks?
